    <text id="B2001T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Tukey asks how to get in touch with W. H. Woodbury, and what travel arrangements
                    exist for teachers.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">H. S. Evans, <abbr expan="Assistant Adjutant General"
                            >A.A.G.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-08-27"><abbr expan="August">Aug</abbr> 27 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Will you have the kindness to inform me where I shall direct a Letter so it will
                    reach <abbr expan="Professor">Prof.</abbr> Woodbury, also to inform me what the
                    arrangements are for the transportation of Teachers from their homes to their
                    respective places of duty, that is whether they travel on all
                    <unclear>Rounds</unclear> not <abbr expan="Government">Govt</abbr> at half fare.</p>

                <p>If you will do this you will greatly oblige your</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Humble Servant</salute>
                    <signed>F.S. Tukey<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst Supt</abbr>
                        Freedmen &amp;c</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
